Fraction absorbed, i.e., only a fraction of the dapagliflozin in the intestinal lumen is absorbed. This parameter determines how much of the dapagliflozin is excreted.

assignmentRule.name: Sum of dapagliflozin and d3g urine

body.p: log(2) ~ 0.693 used for conversion of half-life injection time to injection rate.
Renal threshold glucose.

The renal threshold for glucose (RTG) is the plasma glucose concentration at which tubular reabsorption of glucose begins to saturate; glucose is excreted into the urine in direct proportion to the glucose concentration above this threshold. 12.3 - 12.7 mM RTG (placebo) [Devineni2012]
Urinary glucose excretion is calculated from cumulative amount of glucose in urine.
Possibly catalyzed by OAT3 with Ki=33µM. [FDA]
Possibly catalyzed by OAT3 with Km=115µM. [FDA]
Swallowing, dissolution of tablet, and transport into intestine. Overall process describing the rates of this processes.
